					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">One thing to look out for: the most popular ASIC mappers were in surface mount packages, not DIP, so you'll need various converters to plug them into your harness.<br /><br />edit: Browsing through nescartdb, there are a significant number of infrequently-used 0.1&quot; DIP ones: RAMBO-1 (m64), MIMC-1 (one of two ICs embodied by m206), many of Taito (X1-005 = m80, TC0350 = m33 or m48), Sunsoft 1,2,4 (m184, m89 or m93, m68), TC-112 (m193), Konami's VRC1,2,3,4,6,7 (m75, m21-m26, m73, m85), Irem's (TAM-S1 = m97, H3001 = m65), Codemasters CME-01and Camerica's BF909x (m71), Acclaim's MC-ACC (m4 mmc3 clone??)</div>

					
